<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

    <head>

        <meta charset="UTF-8" >

        <link rel="stylesheet" href="introduction-to-html5.css">

        <title>Introduction to HTML5</title>

    </head>

    <body><!--Comments and explanations in HTML code -->

        <header><h2>Document header</h2><p>This document introduces some of the key semantic elements in HTML5</p>

        <p>This is the document header. This document has been styled to show a border and a margin round every element, and padding between the element and its contents.</p>

        </header>

        <nav>Navigation elements within the page or between content pages in the same site.</nav>

        <main>

            <header>

                <h1>Introduction to HTML5</h1>

            </header>

            <section><h2>A section, part of the main document.</h2></section>

            <section><h2>Another section, Another part of the main document.</h2>

                <section><h3>This is a subsection of the second section.</h3>

                <aside role="note"><p>This is in an aside</p></aside>

                </section></section>

            <section>

                <header><h2>This section has a header</h2><p>And content in the header</p></header><p>And content in the section</p>

                <figure>

                <img src="images/myimage.jpg" alt="my image">   

                <figcaption>This is the caption for the image.</figcaption>

                </figure>

                <footer><p>This section also has a footer</p></footer>

            </section>

            <article><h2>An Article</h2><p>The article is an item that stands by itself - it might be used for content such as reviews or blog comments.</p></article>

        </main>

        <footer><p>This is the footer content for the whole page</p></footer>

    </body>

</html>
